#originalTopic=Debate:_Abortion
Abortion sets precedent of valuing some humans less than others. Ronald Reagan, "Abortion and the Conscience of a Nation", Human Life Review, Spring 1984. - "Regrettably, we live at a time when some persons do not value all human life. They want to pick and choose which individuals have value."[8]
